Patient is a 26-year-old female who presents today with symptoms including migraine, "brain fog", fatigue, low grade fevers, and dizziness that began 6 days ago following receiving her first dose of COVID-19 vaccine. Pt. States she was tested for COVID 3 days prior to vaccine and this was negative. Pt. Says she had been sick for 6-7 days prior to taking vaccine and believes her immune system might of been weak from this. She received Moderna COVID vaccine at hospital. Her symptoms were more persistent and with more intensity for the first 3-4 days but now the symptoms are more "off and on." Her headache is posterior and the dizziness is also "more intermittent than before." Her headache is rated 4/10 at this time. She has taken OTC NSAIDS without much relief. The "dizziness" seems to occur randomly and is not aggravated by rapid positional changes. She does ingest moderate amounts of caffeine to boost her energy level while at work. She denies visual changes/focal weakness/discoordination/nausea/vomiting/abd pain/shortness of breath/wheezing. Pt. Reports that she has been very concerned about making sure she takes the right measures to help prevent getting COVID infection. She has researched the COVID vaccines, how they are made, and which are "more potent."

26 2021-01-25 feeling abnormal, disorientation, confusional state I am not sure if the event that happened Sunday was directly related to the vaccine at all since it ... Read more
Close
I am not sure if the event that happened Sunday was directly related to the vaccine at all since it happened two days later, or if it was just a coincidence, or if the vaccine was just a physical stimulus trigger. I just wanted to let you know just in case! But out of nowhere, I had an episode (never had it before) where I can only describe it as what it might feel like to be drugged. I was delirious, confused, disoriented, dizzy. I wasn't able to leave bed without the room spinning. I had chest tightness and headache. When I would close my eyes, I would feel such head pressure that it felt like my body was on a boat during a tsunami. I would feel shaking and spinning inside my head. I never felt anything like it before. I was struggling to stay conscious. In the moment, I remember wondering if it was a brain aneurysm or if I was dying. I was scared, felt like I needed to call for help, but I was unable to. I allowed myself to fall asleep/lose consciousness (not sure which), and when I woke up an hour or so later, I felt a little better. I was still a bit confused on what happened and felt physically weak, but the episode had resolved. Hours later, I called the on-call service at my doctor's office because I couldn't shake the feeling that something wasn't right. She instructed me to go to the emergency room. By the time I got to the emergency room and got seen, this was a good 8-9 hours or so after the episode occurred. The PA-C at the ER ran bloodwork and a uranalysis (I do not know what he tested for since I was not given the results), as well as had me hooked up to a heart monitor. He said everything looked normal and that he would not run a CT scan since he did not think I had an aneurysm or anything indicating the need to expose me to radiation to perform a CT. I asked for an EEG and he said they do not do that at the emergency room. He discharged me to follow up with my PCP. While in the ER, I would have episodes of staring blankly into space at random, uncontrollably, and for an undetermined amount of time. I told the doctor, and he wasn't concerned. Yesterday (01/25/2021) I met with my PCP via telehealth and explained everything. He thinks it could have been my previously-diagnosed conversion disorder; however, I have not had that manifestation of it in the past. I expressed to him that I am very scared to get the second dose of the vaccine since I do not know if this event is related or not, and I do not want to die. I have two cats who need me! He did not think it was related to the vaccine, since it happened two days after the injection. But conversion disorder comes on with physical/mental/emotional trauma/stimuli. For the most part, I was feeling okay mentally. The vaccine was the only change to my normal routine. My previous conversion disorder effect was the loss/difficulty of the ability to swallow. I have not had an episode of that in years. The symptoms I experienced seem to be possible manifestations of the disorder when I did some research, but it does not fully explain what I experienced. I asked for a referral to neurology, just to be safe, and I have the appointment tomorrow (01/27/2021). I still feel residually weak, slight chest tightness, and overall feeling off/weird. Again, I do not know if this is directly related to the vaccine, but I wanted to make you aware just in case!

12/29/2020- Received the Moderna Vaccine - no pain or problems until 01/04/2021 01/04/2021- Before bedtime my injection site from the Moderna Vaccine became itchy. 01/05/2020- Woke up to a swollen arm (about 3 times the size of my right arm) and the start of a rash (the size of a softball) Was in significant pain and unable to lift my arm. I called the nurse hotline where I received the vaccine. I was told to go to the ER immediately. The ER doctor informed me that they had been seeing this and that their personal vaccine location swelled up as well but went away a few days later. ER doctor gave me Benadryl cream (I can not ingest Benadryl due to an opposite reaction, I become extremely anxious.) The ER doctor informed me that the Benadryl cream wouldn't cause the same reaction. I was sent home with the cream and a wrap. Upon arriving home my rash grew exponentially over the following days. The site became hot (even after icing it) It remained itchy and painful. 01/11/2021- Went to primary care doctor. The rash and swelling had decreased although you could still see the ring of the rash. At this point, my hand was becoming numb after doing daily activities including typing. My palm and thumb area started to turn purplish/blueish when I would type for less than 20 seconds. The doctor told me they would start to reach out to other providers and figure out how to best move forward. In the meantime, there wasn't much to do besides wait and see what happens. 01/13/2021- Woke up throughout the night due to continued pain at the injection site. Called the primary care doctor who wasn't in the office, waited for a call back from their nurse but due delayed call back and increased pain and numbness went to urgent care (which is under the same practice as primary care). The urgent care doctor performed tests regarding pinched nerve shoulder (as they believed I had a pinched nerve in my shoulder) and ordered an x-ray. The x-ray showed tissue damage but nothing else. I was not experiencing shoulder pain, although during one of the shoulder tests I found more discomfort in my left should (injection arm) than my right arm. Therefore, the primary care doctor thought I was experiencing a pinched nerve in my shoulder. 01/14/2021 - Primary care doctor called and informed me they had spoken with the infectious disease doctor in the area who informed them that they have been seeing a similar reaction amongst other people. (7 days after inject, swelling and rash) The infectious disease doctor reported they hadn't seen numbness. The primary care doctor advised me to wait 2 weeks to see how symptoms change before performing additional tests. The primary care doctor also advised me after speaking with the infectious disease doctor to not take the second shot. 01/16/2021- still experiencing issues with daily functioning. Still experiencing numbness in hand and arm. Still experiencing redness around the injection site (although much better still flairs up at moments) Side note: 01/03/2021 - Went cross country skiing, did fall backwards but did NOT fall on arm. Also confusion remains if I was supposed to report this or if the primary care doctor/ER doctor reported this, therefore, urgent care doctor told me to report this reaction.

This spontaneous case was reported by a pharmacist and describes the occurrence of HALLUCINATION (hallucinations) and ANAPHYLACTIC REACTION (severe allergic reaction/anaphylaxis) in a 30-year-old female patient who received mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (batch no. 031A21A) for COVID-19 vaccination. On 17-Mar-2021, the patient experienced ANAPHYLACTIC REACTION (severe allergic reaction/anaphylaxis) (seriousness criterion hospitalization) and ACCIDENTAL OVERDOSE (accidentally given a 3 ml dose of the Moderna Covid-19 vaccine instead of 0.5 ml). On 24-Mar-2021, the patient experienced HALLUCINATION (hallucinations) (seriousness criterion medically significant). For mRNA-1273 (Moderna COVID-19 Vaccine) (Intramuscular), the reporter did not provide any causality assessments. The patient did not have any psychological history; this was the first time she experienced hallucinations. Treatment for the severe allergic reaction/anaphylaxis included intravenous steroids and hydrocortisone. Treatment for hallucinations included droperidol and lorazepam. Based on the current available information and temporal association between the use of the product and the start date of the event (anaphylactic reaction), a causal relationship cannot be excluded. Very limited information regarding the events (Hallucination, anaphylactic reaction, sleep terror, fear of death, delusion, and formication) has been provided at this time. This report refers to a case of (accidental overdose) for mRNA-1273, lot # 031A21A. Further information has been requested. Severe muscle tension in cramping in right arm two hours after injection. In less than 24 hours the muscle cramping had extended up my neck into my face, specifically the masseter muscle of my jaw. I also experienced some numbness on the right side of my face (unfortunately the locked masseter muscle was very noticeable). I was not able to sleep or eat when the pain built; hot and cold temperatures were highly reactive when trying to consume anything. I saw my dentist for an emergency medical appointment on Monday 1/25/2021 with the dentist. I saw Dr. who prescribed a muscle relaxer and assisted me in identifying the masseter muscle as the source of pain and tension as well as exercises that could be done to treat the reaction. While there is no definitive evidence that the muscle cramping is directly related to the COVID vaccine, it is reasonable to suspect that it may have impacted the muscle tension and resulting locked masseter muscle that required clinical intervention. The muscle relaxer was somewhat helpful, however for my body and biochemistry, taking 400mg of ibruprofen every 6-8 hours was much more successful in treating the symptoms.

The events occurred on the same day after the administration of the first dose of mRNA 1273 (Lot # 026L20A, expiration date unknown). Treatment administered include diphenhydramine and epinephrine. Outcome is resolved. Based on the information provided, which indicates a strong temporal association of the reported events with the administration of mRNA-1273 vaccine, a causal association cannot be excluded. Since receiving the Moderna COVID-19 vaccine on 12/30/2020 I have been experiencing what almost feels like brain fog. I have had some trouble staying on task at work, trouble finding words, remembering common last names, etc. Oftentimes I will have this temporarily as a migraine aura, but it typically goes away once the migraine comes and goes. This seems to have come to stay since receiving the vaccine. I did have fatigue for approximately 3 days after the vaccine administration - 2-3 hour naps daily. This has improved some. I also had a dull headache that seemed to be there daily for approximately 2.5 weeks post vaccine- nothing I could not tolerate but it just did not want to go away even with my usual treatment - Excedrin Headache and ice. The best way I can describe it is a dull pain all over the top of my head and forehead. I did have one headache that occurred approximately 5 days after the vaccine, that I would consider a "bad migraine" (Migraine that rendered me incapable of completing my daily routine - having to stay in bed, dizziness, etc). My face on the side with the weakness as a result of my brain tumor has also been a bit more "tired" than usual - facial palsy more pronounced. There have been times in my brain tumor journey where this happens for sometimes a couple of weeks at a time usually due to stress or an impending "bad migraine" coming on or if I have been exposed to or end up developing an illness later - but I never developed an illness an no additional stress. Facial symptoms include smile not as symmetrical (basically more assymetrical than usual - not wanting to move at all so much on the affected side) and more eye watering on the affected side. I do still feel a little lightheaded at times, but otherwise no other neurological symptoms. No upper respiratory symptoms or any other "COVID-like" symptoms. No nausea, vomiting, numbness, or tingling. Symptoms do seem to be improving this week.

On 08-Jan-2020, the patient received vaccine, which was of lack of correct administration as it was injected in the fat and not in the muscle and injection which was appears to be lower than where normally given. On the same date, after administration of vaccine, the patient had experienced swollen arm (swelling), hives on the back, 2.5in red circle, didn't feel good, was tired and couldn't process things well. The event lack of correct administration, injection appears to be lower than where normally given, was injected in the fat and not in the muscle was considered to be resolved on 08-Jan-2021. The event of large-red allergic reaction at the injection site with perfect circle which was hot to the touch developed 10 days after the vaccine administration. Based on the information provided which includes a temporal association, a causal association between the administration of the vaccine and the other reported events cannot be excluded. She was given the vaccine at 12:00. At 12:07 she (she is an RN employee here at the hospital) reported feeling as if she had lump in her throat and asked for some benadryl. Rapid response team was called at 12:08 as she became diaphoretic, flushed and reported blurred vision. MD ordered an IV to be started and a NS bolus x 1 liter. She broke out in hives on bilateral upper extremities. Benadryl, solumedrol, albuterol inhaler, zofran, scopolamine patch were all ordered and given to the patient. She reported that she felt some better and was transferred to the ER at 1245 for further monitoring.

Evening of 2nd approximately 6pm diarrhea began with increasing frequency throughout the night. Lasted through the night several times an hour into the next morning. Around midnight dizziness,, faint and muscle weakness set in with feeling of extreme pressure on neck, especially right side where shot administered. Arms became tingly, tongue became tingly, hard to keep awake. After 12 hrs of extreme diarrhea, passed out for 12hrs straight. Awoke dehydrated, extreme muscle weakness unable to walk or stand, light headed, nauseous, dizzy, unable to grip or exert force. Felt like head was detached from body due to extreme pressure on neck. Rapid resting heart rate in 90s (usual testing HR in 50s). Constant rolling waves of abdominal cramps brought dizziness with each cramp, acid reflux, bloating and gas. These symptoms lasted through the evening of the 3rd into the 4th. Considered going to ER for help, as extreme dizziness and muscle weakness prevented walking. Fell asleep. 6am March 4th developed fever of 101. Continued extreme dizziness, pressure on neck, muscle weakness and feeling faint and extreme lethargy throughout day. Fever subsided to 99 by evening of 4th. Ate plain rice evening of 4th, 1st time eating in over 48hrs. Immediately passed out. Match 5th still feeling weak, hard to stand, limited walking. Diarrhea has subsided, less pressure on neck and less dizziness. Feeling exhausted overall. Fall asleep easily and randomly.

an internal vibrating tremor inside of her body; flu like symptoms; high blood pressure; insomnia; increase pulse; Dilated pupils; A spontaneous report was received from a healthcare professional concerning a 39-year-old, female patient who received Modern's COVID-19 vaccine (mRNA-1273) and experienced flu like symptoms, a feeling of an internal vibrating tremor inside of her body/tremor, high blood pressure/increased blood pressure, insomnia, dilated pupil/mydriasis and increase pulse/heart rate increased. The patient's medical history was not provided. No relevant concomitant medications were reported. On 24-Jan-2021, prior to the onset of the events, the patient received the second dose of two planned doses of mRNA-1273 (lot/batch: unknown)on left arm for prophylaxis of COVID-19 infection. On 25-Jan-2021, The patient experienced flu like symptoms, but in the afternoon of the same day she also started to experience an internal "vibrating" tremor inside of her body. She had this symptom for 4 weeks now along with high blood pressure, insomnia, dilated pupils and increase pulse. A neurologist told her that it could be an adrenergic hyper response to the vaccine. No Laboratory details provided. Treatment information provided was beta blockers prescribed in the ER visit. Action taken with mRNA-1273 in response to the events is not applicable. At the time of this report, the outcome of the events experienced flu like symptoms, a feeling of an internal vibrating tremor inside of her body, high blood pressure, insomnia, dilated pupil and increase pulse is Unknown.; Reporter's Comments: This case concerns a 39 Y/O F with a serious unexpected event of tremor and NS unexpected influenza like illness, blood pressure increased, heart rate increased, mydriasis, insomnia, and possibly a "adrenergic hyper response to the vaccine". Treated with beta blockers. Event onset 2 days after first dose mRNA-1273. Outcome unknown. Based on current available information and temporal association between use of the product and the start date of the event, a causal relationship cannot be excluded.
